-- Lorillard Net Income Rises 26% as Newport Brand Increases Market Share
-- Chris Burritt
-- 2010-04-26T20:15:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-26/lorillard-profit-rises-26-as-newport-cigarette-brand-gains-market-share.html

          
          
             Lorillard Inc., the third-largest
U.S. cigarette maker, said first-quarter profit rose 26 percent
after its top-selling Newport brand added market share.  
 Net income advanced 26 percent to $232 million, or $1.50 a
share, from $184 million, or $1.09, a year earlier, the
Greensboro, North Carolina-based company said today in a
statement. Analysts predicted $1.22, the average of nine
estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  
 Newport, the biggest-selling U.S. menthol cigarette,
increased its market share by 75 basis points to 10.9 percent,
the company said. Lorillardâ€™s shipments rose 12 percent to 8.86
billion cigarettes from the same quarter a year earlier.  
 Lorillard fell 70 cents to $78.87 at 4:01 p.m. in New York
Stock Exchange composite trading. The shares have dropped 1.7
percent this year.  
